{"type": "assistant", "message": {"id": "msg_1784638277797", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "tool_use", "id": "chatcmpl-tool-91a65389d3e886ee", "name": "Bash", "input": {"command": "curl -sL \"https://arxiv.org/abs/2606.03747\" -o /tmp/prior_abs.html 2>&1; python3 -c \"\nimport re, html\nwith open('/tmp/prior_abs.html','r',encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    h = f.read()\ntext = re.sub(r'<script.*?</script>', '', h, flags=re.S)\ntext = re.sub(r'<style.*?</style>', '', text, flags=re.S)\ntext = re.sub(r'<[^>]+>', ' ', text)\ntext = html.unescape(text)\ntext = re.sub(r'\\s+', ' ', text)\n# find abstract\nidx = text.find('Abstract')\nprint(text[idx:idx+3000] if idx>=0 else text[:3000])\n\" 2>&1", "description": "Get prior paper abstract"}}], "model": "GLM-5.2-w4a8", "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 0, "output_tokens": 0, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 0}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "f31f4fa1-616a-4ad1-93c7-474263ce4b1c", "uuid": "6406be07-e3b5-4e73-9671-478325af5977"}
{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-91a65389d3e886ee", "type": "tool_result", "content": "Abstract: Audio-Visual Event Recognition (AVER) is essential for intelligent urban monitoring systems, where robust multimodal understanding of complex environments is required. This paper proposes a stable hybrid cross-attention fusion framework for audio-visual event recognition in smart urban environments. The proposed architecture combines pretrained Video Masked Autoencoder (VideoMAE) and Audio Spectrogram Transformer (AST) representations with FiLM-based audio conditioning, bidirectional cross-attention fusion, multimodal Transformer encoding, and modality-temporal attention. To improve computational efficiency and training stability, frozen pretrained backbones and cached feature extraction are employed. Extensive experiments on the AVE dataset show that the proposed framework achieves the highest average performance among the evaluated unimodal and multimodal baselines across multiple evaluation metrics, obtaining a best validation accuracy of 91.74% and a test accuracy of 83.85 plus/minus 1.40% over five independent runs. The results indicate that the proposed hybrid fusion strategy effectively captures complementary audio-visual information and provides robust multimodal representation learning for challenging realworld urban monitoring scenarios. Comments: 6 pages, 4 Figures Subjects: Audio and Speech Processing (eess.AS) ; Signal Processing (eess.SP) Cite as: arXiv:2606.03747 [eess.AS] (or arXiv:2606.03747v1 [eess.AS] for this version) https://doi.org/10.48550/arXiv.2606.03747 Focus to learn more arXiv-issued DOI via DataCite Submission history From: Parinaz Binandeh Dehaghani [ view email ] [v1] Tue, 2 Jun 2026 15:01:06 UTC (1,926 KB) Full-text links: Access Paper: View a PDF of the paper titled Stable Hybrid Cross-Attention Fusion for Audio-Visual Event Recognition, by Parinaz Binandeh Dehaghani and 2 other autho